Class S3ServiceInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.cloud.service.BaseServiceInfo
      • com.emc.ecs.connector.S3ServiceInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.cloud.service.ServiceInfo

    public class S3ServiceInfo
extends org.springframework.cloud.service.BaseServiceInfo
    Provides a normalized implementation of S3 service details which can be gleaned in multiple cloud environments. This class includes all of the necessary parameters to create a valid S3Connector.

        public S3ServiceInfo(java.lang.String id,
                     java.lang.String accessKey,
                     java.lang.String secretKey,
                     java.lang.String endpoint,
                     java.lang.String bucket)
        Default Constructor. The default constructor requires all fields to be provided; however, in some cases fields fields will be provided as null values.
        Parameters:
        id - the service ID of the provisioned service
        accessKey - the user access-key used to authenticate a connection or requests
        secretKey - the user secret-key used to authenticate a connection or requests
        endpoint - (optional) the S3 compatible URL or endpoint of the S3 service
        bucket - (optional) a specific bucket the client is expected to address calls to storage
